cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel meta-learning model that adapts to varying task distributions and considers distributional differences in unseen tasks. This involves balancing the effect of meta-learning and task-specific learning, which is a common theme in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning to Learn" or "Meta-Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also deals with classification tasks, which can be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of Bayesian inference and variational inference suggests a focus on probabilistic modeling and uncertainty estimation, which can be associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
